---
import { type Lang } from "@/i18n"

type Props = { lang: Lang }
const { lang } = Astro.props
---

<prose-content>
  {lang === "zh" ? (
    <>
      <h1>关于</h1>
      <p>说实话,我开这个博客,一半是为了对付自己的不安。</p>
      <p>
        这世界变得太快。每隔一阵就有人告诉你"一切都不一样了",可没人说得清到底哪里变了、变了多少。我受不了这种悬空感——所以我习惯钻进数据里,把一件事到底发生了什么弄清楚,钉死。钉死了,我自己才踏实一点。
      </p>
      <p>
        「枢机」就是这些被钉下来的判断。它们大多听着像"暴论":过头,但每一个背后都有数据。我尽量写得冷静——不是因为我没情绪,恰恰相反,是这些题我太有情绪,只有冷下来才不至于把话说歪。
      </p>
      <p>
        判断有对有错,我认。但我宁可把话说死、将来被打脸,也不写那种四平八稳、谁都不得罪、读完等于没读的东西。
      </p>
      <p>
        如果你也老觉得脚下的地在晃,想找几块还算结实的石头踩——进来坐。订阅 <a href="/zh/rss.xml">RSS</a>,或读 <a href="/about">English</a>。
      </p>
    </>
  ) : (
    <>
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>Honestly, half the reason I started this blog is to fight my own unease.</p>
      <p>
        The world changes too fast. Every other week someone tells you
        "everything is different now," but no one can say exactly what changed,
        or by how much. I can't stand that floating feeling — so I dig into the
        data until I know what actually happened, and I nail it down. Nailing it
        down is the only thing that steadies me.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Seam is those nailed-down judgments. Most read as "hot takes" — they
        sound like too much, but every one has data under it. I try to write
        coldly, not because I feel nothing, but the opposite: these topics get
        to me, and staying cold is the only way I keep from bending the truth to
        fit the mood.
      </p>
      <p>
        Some calls will be right, some wrong; I'll own them. But I'd rather say
        something definite and eat the consequences than write the safe,
        offend-no-one stuff you finish and realize you've read nothing.
      </p>
      <p>
        If the ground under you always feels like it's shifting, and you want a
        few solid stones to stand on — pull up a chair. Subscribe via
        <a href="/rss.xml"> RSS</a>, or read in <a href="/zh/about">中文</a>.
      </p>
    </>
  )}
</prose-content>
